where B$2 is the month header (January, February, …) and $A5 is the category name for that row. This formula works for all month columns (B‑M) and all category rows (starting at row 5) without hard‑coding row limits. We will write the formula into each empty cell in that range, preserve existing formulas (e.g., the total column N), save the workbook, recalculate, and then verify a few cells to ensure they contain the expected formulas and non‑None values after recalculation.
